1
00:00:12,875 --> 00:00:22,516
<i>The sky is blossoming with stars,</i>

2
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:30,998
<i>The evening's wreathing lights.</i>

3
00:00:34,375 --> 00:00:41,506
<i>Oh, the nights, Donetsk nights,</i>

4
00:00:43,458 --> 00:00:47,844
<i>years of my youth.</i>

5
00:01:51,873 --> 00:01:53,560
What do you want?

6
00:02:02,236 --> 00:02:07,496
FLOWER ON A STONE

7
00:02:07,684 --> 00:02:12,940
<i>Oleksandr Dovzhenko
Kyiv Film Studio</i>

8
00:02:15,792 --> 00:02:17,841
Why did you do this?

9
00:02:18,628 --> 00:02:20,482
I couldn't do in other way.

10
00:02:21,449 --> 00:02:23,185
I'm conscious again.

11
00:02:24,042 --> 00:02:25,083
Sorry...

12
00:02:27,509 --> 00:02:30,425
Fine, we'll talk later.
Now go to bed, take a rest.

13
00:02:31,526 --> 00:02:32,915
Don't go, doctor!

14
00:02:34,022 --> 00:02:35,319
Stay.

15
00:02:37,735 --> 00:02:39,151
Let's come up, doctor.

16
00:03:04,265 --> 00:03:05,704
Birds...

17
00:03:06,799 --> 00:03:08,072
Can you hear?

18
00:03:10,901 --> 00:03:12,308
- Doctor?
- What?

19
00:03:13,207 --> 00:03:15,027
Do you know, these trees...

20
00:03:15,609 --> 00:03:16,849
are just one year old?

21
00:03:17,492 --> 00:03:19,805
I don't, I'm... a newcomer.

22
00:03:21,687 --> 00:03:24,748
- Then you do not know how things began.
- No.

23
00:03:35,317 --> 00:03:39,408
<i>The new city will arise here
despite arrogant neighbour!</i>

24
00:03:39,751 --> 00:03:41,724
Komsomolska mine will be built here

25
00:03:42,458 --> 00:03:44,164
<i>Hop Out, Everyone!</i>

26
00:04:02,389 --> 00:04:03,634
Just look!

27
00:04:05,708 --> 00:04:07,208
Smile!

28
00:04:07,792 --> 00:04:09,132
Like it?!

29
00:04:13,373 --> 00:04:17,333
- What about speeches, orchestra?
- Where will we receive mail?

30
00:04:17,405 --> 00:04:19,536
Liuda, where will I live with my wife?

31
00:04:22,831 --> 00:04:27,334
- Hey! They are coming!
- Coming!

32
00:04:34,292 --> 00:04:37,677
Donetsk salutation
to respected Komsomol!

33
00:04:38,223 --> 00:04:39,874
<i>Salute!</i>

34
00:04:45,188 --> 00:04:48,237
- Who are you?
- Let me introduce!

35
00:04:49,996 --> 00:04:52,296
Hryhorii Hryva. Mine drifter.

36
00:04:53,722 --> 00:04:55,295
You drifted a lot, yeah?

37
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:59,444
If following you - to the world's end!

38
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:09,450
<i>"Be Aware of blue eyes and
black brows", - father warned.</i>

39
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:12,702
You had to listen to your father!

40
00:05:15,292 --> 00:05:16,942
Meteoric decision...

41
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:18,751
Today we dance.

42
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:21,217
Tomorrow go to restaurant
to solidify relations.

43
00:05:21,623 --> 00:05:22,986
After tomorrow we get married.

44
00:05:23,042 --> 00:05:26,623
And you move to my flat
as a legal wife!

45
00:05:29,105 --> 00:05:31,273
What if I do not want to?

46
00:05:32,243 --> 00:05:35,146
- Do you know who speaks to you?
- Who?

47
00:05:35,682 --> 00:05:38,339
He's the beauty and pride of Donbas!

48
00:05:39,373 --> 00:05:40,652
Hryhorii Hryva!

49
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:44,403
Let your beauty and pride... wait!

50
00:05:45,879 --> 00:05:47,620
I will dance with him...

51
00:05:48,875 --> 00:05:51,000
when he learns how to ask!

52
00:05:52,471 --> 00:05:53,924
Are you gonna teach me?

53
00:05:56,222 --> 00:05:59,336
Listen... She’s not alone here.

54
00:06:02,914 --> 00:06:05,623
- I see nobody.
- You'd better do.

55
00:06:06,168 --> 00:06:08,438
<i>They are coming! Coming!</i>

56
00:06:10,213 --> 00:06:12,110
Hey! Why are you nipping off?

57
00:06:12,474 --> 00:06:14,787
Wait! Let’s go to the restaurant!

58
00:06:14,997 --> 00:06:17,945
<i>Look! More fiancés are coming!</i>

59
00:06:18,167 --> 00:06:20,594
<i>These ones are richer! Driving Volga!</i>

60
00:06:26,988 --> 00:06:29,533
- Good morning!
- Greetings!

61
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,700
- Who are you?
- Me?

62
00:06:34,949 --> 00:06:37,813
I’m... future boss...

63
00:06:38,918 --> 00:06:40,211
of the future mine.

64
00:06:40,648 --> 00:06:42,782
- Comrade Varchenko?
- Pavlo Fedorovych.

65
00:06:43,799 --> 00:06:45,054
And I’m Komsomol leader.

66
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,667
That’s might.

67
00:08:05,173 --> 00:08:09,819
<i>Where blue mountains are...</i>

68
00:08:10,770 --> 00:08:14,436
<i>the Carpathian mountains,</i>

69
00:08:16,547 --> 00:08:25,407
<i>fog floats over the valleys...</i>

70
00:08:27,167 --> 00:08:29,685
You’ll go to the Donbas,

71
00:08:30,509 --> 00:08:32,271
to be building the mine...

72
00:08:32,351 --> 00:08:34,758
It will be hard there, but...

73
00:08:35,042 --> 00:08:39,794
in the hardness souls are reaching for God...

74
00:08:40,165 --> 00:08:43,404
You’ll work hard, become a role model,

75
00:08:43,454 --> 00:08:46,453
find friends - reliable, faithful.

76
00:08:47,553 --> 00:08:49,380
I will come in a year.

77
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:52,490
We’ll get together brothers, sisters...

78
00:08:53,624 --> 00:08:56,010
organise big family...

79
00:08:56,707 --> 00:08:58,627
and glorify God.

80
00:08:59,186 --> 00:09:01,779
I will glorify God here and
ask for His mercy...

81
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:05,169
- No-no-no, it is needed there.
- And here.

82
00:09:06,513 --> 00:09:08,945
- Khrystyna...
- I can’t!

83
00:09:09,304 --> 00:09:10,804
Khrystyna.

84
00:10:26,214 --> 00:10:27,513
Hryva?

85
00:10:29,526 --> 00:10:30,883
Why are you here?

86
00:10:34,435 --> 00:10:35,489
I’m dreaming.

87
00:10:36,992 --> 00:10:39,956
Dreaming? What about?

88
00:10:44,629 --> 00:10:48,139
Who wants to know everything,
will age quickly,

89
00:10:48,875 --> 00:10:50,808
mademoiselle Komsomol lead.

90
00:10:58,755 --> 00:11:01,608
Come inside the tent! Let’s dance!

91
00:11:04,082 --> 00:11:05,524
You invite me.

92
00:11:08,126 --> 00:11:11,098
But you’ll dance with me.
Me only.

93
00:11:13,057 --> 00:11:14,653
Is it your rule?

94
00:11:16,625 --> 00:11:17,826
My rule.

95
00:11:17,875 --> 00:11:20,005
<i>Liuda Kharko, Liuda!</i>

96
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:23,125
Liuda! Take it! Letter for you!

97
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:26,292
It’s got wet, sorry!
A newspaper, a magazine!

98
00:11:27,167 --> 00:11:29,844
Oh, parcel for Dzhaparidze. Dzhaparidze!

99
00:11:31,583 --> 00:11:32,970
From home...

100
00:12:25,625 --> 00:12:27,166
Khrystyna...

101
00:12:27,792 --> 00:12:29,845
Cross the doorstep of my home.

102
00:12:38,316 --> 00:12:41,355
I was waiting for you
impatiently, dear sister.

103
00:12:42,703 --> 00:12:48,021
Enter my house and lift with us
your soul towards God.

104
00:12:52,562 --> 00:12:55,312
From your father? Thank you.

105
00:12:56,049 --> 00:12:57,612
Come in, sister, come in.

106
00:13:02,123 --> 00:13:04,192
From now on this house is your house.

107
00:13:05,291 --> 00:13:07,590
Our souls are always opened for you,

108
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:10,599
as the doors of my house.

109
00:13:11,083 --> 00:13:12,118
Sit.

110
00:13:21,771 --> 00:13:22,972
In time of need...

111
00:13:23,779 --> 00:13:27,007
when a heavy stone
is on your friends’ souls...

112
00:13:28,086 --> 00:13:30,083
remind them of God.

113
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:38,257
In this house they will always find
solace, peace and love.

114
00:13:39,958 --> 00:13:41,698
God is love.

115
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:53,761
We get closer to God through soul,

116
00:13:54,783 --> 00:13:56,353
not through the cross...

117
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:05,559
God is love.

118
00:14:22,792 --> 00:14:25,762
Come in, dear sister.

119
00:14:30,138 --> 00:14:32,726
- "How the Steel Was Tempered".
- Well, fine.

120
00:14:33,506 --> 00:14:36,484
- "Gadfly" by Voynich.
- My favorite book!

121
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:37,717
Here...

122
00:14:39,917 --> 00:14:40,917
Please.

123
00:14:42,812 --> 00:14:45,685
I can offer you some
anti-religious literature.

124
00:14:46,895 --> 00:14:48,659
Of sectarians, Jehovah’s Witnesses.

125
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:51,978
About orthodox clerics.

126
00:14:52,724 --> 00:14:54,284
I would say these people are worse

127
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:56,333
than your cardinal Montanelli.

128
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:11,874
Clerics say a lot of God,

129
00:15:12,494 --> 00:15:15,320
but forget about the human soul.

130
00:15:15,448 --> 00:15:17,926
But human soul is such
a complex instrument.

131
00:15:18,271 --> 00:15:21,035
Don't you have a book
about Pentecostals?

132
00:15:21,781 --> 00:15:24,271
Comrade Varchenko, just in time!

133
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:26,441
Remarque is waiting for you.

134
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:29,041
Here you are.

135
00:15:30,046 --> 00:15:32,485
Thanks. So, don’t you have
this kind of book?

136
00:15:32,574 --> 00:15:33,979
Sadly, no.

137
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:37,614
Nevertheless, in the encyclopaedia...

138
00:15:38,234 --> 00:15:40,926
volume 38, page 399...

139
00:15:40,975 --> 00:15:43,785
There is nothing essential
about sectarians.

140
00:15:44,292 --> 00:15:46,008
Sectarians in Islam, in Buddhism...

141
00:15:46,293 --> 00:15:50,034
It's history... But I'm preoccupied
with nowadays.

142
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,625
Pentecostals.

143
00:15:52,583 --> 00:15:55,437
Well, what I would say:
it's a small, unremarkable sect.

144
00:15:55,875 --> 00:15:57,529
No wonder, nobody is writing.

145
00:15:57,958 --> 00:15:59,000
Pavlo Fedorovych!

146
00:15:59,393 --> 00:16:01,822
Comrade Zabroda, obviously,
learnt this issue deeply.

147
00:16:02,394 --> 00:16:04,383
Let’s ask him to make a lecture?

148
00:16:04,471 --> 00:16:06,004
You try, make a deal.

149
00:16:06,977 --> 00:16:09,351
Come on, what a lecturer am I?

150
00:16:09,747 --> 00:16:13,044
I even be ashamed
to speak to the audience.

151
00:16:13,402 --> 00:16:14,472
Dare to try.

152
00:16:15,187 --> 00:16:17,885
Thanks for your regard,
but this job's not for me.

153
00:16:19,292 --> 00:16:21,145
Ventilation is so poor here.

154
00:16:21,588 --> 00:16:23,806
I'd better find a new space for you.

155
00:16:24,883 --> 00:16:27,587
Not for you. For Pentecos... Ugh!

156
00:16:29,316 --> 00:16:30,608
For the book storage.

157
00:16:34,424 --> 00:16:35,766
<i>Unload faster!</i>

158
00:16:39,642 --> 00:16:41,403
- Your books.
- Thanks.

159
00:16:42,459 --> 00:16:46,637
- Have you ever been in the mine?
- No. Take me, Pavlo Fedorovych!

160
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:49,480
Sit.

161
00:16:50,618 --> 00:16:52,171
Some Komsomol leader you are... 

162
00:16:53,118 --> 00:16:55,885
Come again, Pavlo Fedorovych.
We can make a subscription.

163
00:17:05,708 --> 00:17:09,698
- Look, Komsomol, what mine is.
- Is it your first time?

164
00:17:52,108 --> 00:17:55,432
- An actress?
- Even worse.

165
00:17:55,697 --> 00:17:57,955
- A journalist!
- Guess again!

166
00:17:59,157 --> 00:18:01,978
- Pavlo Fedorovych, can I go there?
- Go ahead.

167
00:18:04,196 --> 00:18:06,005
<i>Just be careful.</i>

168
00:18:16,251 --> 00:18:18,593
- Vasia!
- Come on!

169
00:18:20,423 --> 00:18:21,555
Watch, where are you going!

170
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:27,803
- Komsomol!
- Hello!

171
00:18:28,167 --> 00:18:30,341
- Staring here?
- Yes!

172
00:18:30,481 --> 00:18:34,731
- Can I bring our fellows here?
- Not all at once.

173
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:41,810
- Foreman, what's going on?
- It’s all right!

174
00:18:42,555 --> 00:18:47,696
<i>- It seemed the hammer has fallen!
- It’s all right!</i>

175
00:19:05,056 --> 00:19:07,468
- Thank you, Pavlo Fedorovych.
- Thank to the master.

176
00:19:07,561 --> 00:19:09,140
Did you like it?

177
00:19:09,542 --> 00:19:12,406
A bit scary first.
And then I used to.

178
00:19:16,859 --> 00:19:20,187
- Can I bring the guys here?
- Sure, you can.

179
00:19:21,291 --> 00:19:22,640
But not all of them at once.

180
00:19:23,773 --> 00:19:26,268
- Well, I got to go...
- Maybe, tea?

181
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:28,785
No, I’m in a hurry.

182
00:19:31,655 --> 00:19:32,946
Well, you're in charge now...

183
00:19:34,769 --> 00:19:36,600
Tomorrow I’ll bring
all the lads to the mine.

184
00:19:39,136 --> 00:19:41,063
One will go to the mine,

185
00:19:42,054 --> 00:19:44,345
but another... to the sect.

186
00:19:44,955 --> 00:19:45,986
Do you know such people?

187
00:19:49,792 --> 00:19:51,884
- I know...
- You know who?

188
00:19:53,544 --> 00:19:55,266
- I know...
- What're you gonna do?

189
00:19:57,013 --> 00:19:59,914
I’ve... sent a letter to her father.

190
00:20:02,630 --> 00:20:05,545
Well-well. Made a favour...
for the old man.

191
00:20:06,917 --> 00:20:08,792
But he’s a sectarian himself!

192
00:20:10,875 --> 00:20:12,031
Then...

193
00:20:12,732 --> 00:20:14,764
Then I’ll chew her out at the meeting!

194
00:20:15,547 --> 00:20:17,104
I’ll chew her out!

195
00:20:18,087 --> 00:20:22,415
They promise her love
and peace in their house.

196
00:20:23,734 --> 00:20:25,170
And you want to scold her...

197
00:20:28,330 --> 00:20:31,193
Liuda... What time are you living in?

198
00:21:09,879 --> 00:21:11,162
Pardon?

199
00:21:13,826 --> 00:21:15,339
- Welcome.
- Pasha.

200
00:21:27,573 --> 00:21:30,219
- Ordered yet?
- Two homemade noodle soups.

201
00:21:33,949 --> 00:21:35,225
Shakespeare.

202
00:21:37,625 --> 00:21:38,774
Sonnets.

203
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:43,070
Tonia! Two flasks and my usual appetizer!

204
00:21:43,212 --> 00:21:44,321
Okay.

205
00:21:44,434 --> 00:21:46,117
Your usual appetizer?

206
00:21:46,851 --> 00:21:49,747
- You're like merchant Stroganov.
- Yes.

207
00:21:50,693 --> 00:21:52,213
My usual appetizer.

208
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,209
Appetizer of Hryva the drifter.

209
00:21:59,375 --> 00:22:00,693
- Would you mind?
- No!

210
00:22:10,843 --> 00:22:14,390
Here you are, to your health
and arrival to the Donbas!

211
00:22:16,234 --> 00:22:18,060
I mean you, Komsomol leader.

212
00:22:23,328 --> 00:22:24,370
Too good for it?

213
00:22:27,796 --> 00:22:30,428
- Let's go, Liuda.
- Where do you go?

214
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:40,102
Here you are, please.

215
00:22:42,958 --> 00:22:44,656
- Please.
- Thanks.

216
00:22:51,852 --> 00:22:55,203
Here are your homemade noodle soups.

217
00:22:56,051 --> 00:22:57,477
Many thanks.

218
00:23:04,576 --> 00:23:07,871
But you... we’ll have a special talk.

219
00:23:41,744 --> 00:23:43,079
Give us Spirit, God!

220
00:23:43,428 --> 00:23:45,074
- Glory to Jesus.
- Glory forever.

221
00:23:45,916 --> 00:23:47,471
Give us Spirit, God.

222
00:23:47,876 --> 00:23:49,434
Give us Spirit, God.

223
00:24:08,421 --> 00:24:09,921
You, come here.

224
00:24:10,281 --> 00:24:12,288
Come, don't be afraid.

225
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:22,669
<i>New series of nuclear explosions
was conducted by the USA</i>

226
00:24:22,708 --> 00:24:24,186
<i>near Christmas Island.</i>

227
00:24:25,172 --> 00:24:27,108
<i>This act stressed again...</i>

228
00:24:27,750 --> 00:24:30,351
What's the hell? Beep!

229
00:24:32,142 --> 00:24:33,671
Arsen and Hryva...

230
00:24:37,828 --> 00:24:40,173
Well, you fight, fight.
Let's see, who’s stronger.

231
00:24:42,687 --> 00:24:44,421
I sacrificed two sons to the war.

232
00:24:45,505 --> 00:24:49,343
So that you, two lads,
could maim each other? 


233
00:24:50,034 --> 00:24:51,210
Is that it?

234
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:55,107
Get in the car, Arsen.



235
00:24:56,735 --> 00:24:58,481
And you, Hryva, leave.

236
00:25:20,326 --> 00:25:23,658
- What’s the business between you?
- Pavlo Fedorovych...

237
00:25:25,689 --> 00:25:27,305
What should I do, Pavlo Fedorovych?

238
00:25:27,992 --> 00:25:30,997
- She's a sectarian.
- Who’s a sectarian?

239
00:25:32,380 --> 00:25:34,637
Khrystyna... Khrystyna Ravliuk!

240
00:25:36,029 --> 00:25:37,990
Why do you hang with her?

241
00:25:39,083 --> 00:25:40,653
I love her.

242
00:25:44,060 --> 00:25:45,471
Can you understand, I love.

243
00:25:46,976 --> 00:25:49,727
Tell her about it.

244
00:25:50,606 --> 00:25:52,046
I love you above all!

245
00:25:52,493 --> 00:25:54,493
Love you more than life,
more than sun!

246
00:25:54,542 --> 00:25:56,855
You shouldn't love me!
I beg you!

247
00:25:57,253 --> 00:25:58,561
- I Love!
- No!

248
00:25:59,675 --> 00:26:03,234
Khrystyna! Where are you going, stop!
Khrystyna!

249
00:26:04,824 --> 00:26:06,942
No! No!

250
00:26:08,859 --> 00:26:10,235
Lord!

251
00:26:13,158 --> 00:26:14,861
<i>(whisper) More than life...</i>

252
00:26:15,842 --> 00:26:17,551
<i>I love you...</i>

253
00:26:17,874 --> 00:26:19,196
<i>I love you!</i>

254
00:26:31,528 --> 00:26:34,389
I’m sectarian! I believe in God
and love Him more than life!

255
00:26:34,654 --> 00:26:36,749
You’ve got to know
everything about me.

256
00:26:36,833 --> 00:26:38,554
I know everything about you.

257
00:26:39,614 --> 00:26:41,236
- You know?
- Yes.

258
00:26:42,073 --> 00:26:43,504
- I know...
- And?...

259
00:26:43,993 --> 00:26:45,524
And love me as I am?

260
00:26:47,836 --> 00:26:49,537
I love...

261
00:26:51,794 --> 00:26:54,278
My darling... Beloved...

262
00:26:58,612 --> 00:27:01,969
Join my sect!
And I’ll be your wife!

263
00:27:02,173 --> 00:27:05,612
Faithful and devoted.
Like in God’s face.

264
00:27:11,331 --> 00:27:13,234
I’m waiting for the answer.

265
00:27:19,944 --> 00:27:21,546
You don’t love me.

266
00:27:23,323 --> 00:27:25,611
Fine. Come on.

267
00:27:44,817 --> 00:27:46,497
Let him in.

268
00:27:55,561 --> 00:27:56,671
Greetings.

269
00:27:58,292 --> 00:28:00,565
Brothers and sisters!

270
00:28:03,139 --> 00:28:04,525
Come in.

271
00:28:06,833 --> 00:28:08,333
Brothers and sisters.

272
00:28:09,003 --> 00:28:12,198
Today when we make
our modest offerings...

273
00:28:12,736 --> 00:28:14,035
to God...

274
00:28:14,458 --> 00:28:18,278
Him, the Most High, has brought
to our family a new brother.

275
00:28:19,686 --> 00:28:21,432
Come here, my brother.

276
00:28:25,394 --> 00:28:27,928
- What’s your name?
- Arsen Zahornyi.

277
00:28:29,644 --> 00:28:30,973
Brother Arsen.

278
00:28:32,042 --> 00:28:34,565
God has brought you to us
in a solemn moment.

279
00:28:35,788 --> 00:28:38,857
- It’s a sign of goodness.
- Thanks.

280
00:28:41,366 --> 00:28:43,189
And now, brothers and sisters,

281
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:45,553
let ask God

282
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:48,537
with our infinite love,

283
00:28:48,822 --> 00:28:51,128
and endless devotion,

284
00:28:51,582 --> 00:28:53,070
He accepted from us

285
00:28:53,765 --> 00:28:55,326
our modest offerings.

286
00:28:55,935 --> 00:28:58,684
- Our modest offerings!
- Our modest offerings...

287
00:29:06,375 --> 00:29:07,859
Modest offerings.

288
00:29:13,958 --> 00:29:17,028
Apostle Paul says to us:

289
00:29:17,977 --> 00:29:21,075
The Bible (published in New York): 
<i>"Having livelihood and clothes,</i>

290
00:29:22,268 --> 00:29:24,349
<i>let be satisfied with these.</i>

291
00:29:25,816 --> 00:29:28,303
<i>But who wants to get rich</i>

292
00:29:28,931 --> 00:29:32,288
<i>fall into temptation and netting.</i>

293
00:29:33,954 --> 00:29:36,367
<i>As the root for all evil</i>

294
00:29:37,542 --> 00:29:40,383
<i>is love of money".</i>

295
00:29:42,206 --> 00:29:44,026
Brothers and sisters!

296
00:29:44,075 --> 00:29:47,525
- God accepted all our offerings.
- Oh God!

297
00:29:48,466 --> 00:29:50,462
Truth has been revealed for me...

298
00:29:52,175 --> 00:29:54,514
from our new brother.

299
00:29:56,452 --> 00:29:58,942
God craves faith.

300
00:30:01,061 --> 00:30:03,979
Are you ready to give God...

301
00:30:04,654 --> 00:30:07,518
- ...a drop of blood?
- You mean?

302
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:11,806
Finger of your hand,
which is closer to the heart,

303
00:30:12,281 --> 00:30:15,367
has to be laid under a sacral axe.

304
00:30:22,493 --> 00:30:23,985
Think until the morning.

305
00:30:25,458 --> 00:30:28,814
If you came to us with clear soul,

306
00:30:30,423 --> 00:30:33,524
your faith brings you here again.

307
00:30:35,015 --> 00:30:38,184
And gives drop of blood to God.

308
00:30:40,093 --> 00:30:41,427
Oh God!

309
00:30:51,073 --> 00:30:54,472
- I’m scared, Arsen. I’m scared.
- Be calm, Khrystyna.

310
00:30:54,979 --> 00:30:56,220
Calm.

311
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,456
Chmykh!

312
00:31:03,099 --> 00:31:06,755
- Who is he, this Zahornyi?
- Member of the Komsomol committee!

313
00:31:06,863 --> 00:31:07,964
An intellectual.

314
00:31:09,340 --> 00:31:12,419
- Do you think faith brought him here?
- No.

315
00:31:14,197 --> 00:31:17,114
- What does he want here?
- I don’t know.

316
00:31:19,860 --> 00:31:22,485
I would surprise him
with a single drop of blood.

317
00:31:23,554 --> 00:31:25,554
I’m afraid he won’t come again.

318
00:31:26,088 --> 00:31:27,880
I’ve seen fear in his eyes.

319
00:31:28,688 --> 00:31:30,869
Oh my, weakling.

320
00:32:53,158 --> 00:32:56,038
I will ask God not to accept
from you this sacrifice.

321
00:32:56,537 --> 00:32:58,628
Khrystyna, easy, don’t think of it.

322
00:33:24,458 --> 00:33:26,943
Khrystyna! Buy it, don’t hesitate.

323
00:33:30,157 --> 00:33:34,177
- Hrysha! Which one? I’m confused.
- Choose yourself.

324
00:33:35,245 --> 00:33:38,844
Evening suit, the one in the window.

325
00:33:43,711 --> 00:33:45,907
Size 52. Tall.

326
00:33:51,269 --> 00:33:52,520
Khrystyna, wait a moment.

327
00:33:55,792 --> 00:33:59,331
- Sister! Why did your faith stagger?
- I love him.

328
00:34:00,532 --> 00:34:03,473
God is love. But yours
is not love, but sin!

329
00:34:03,787 --> 00:34:04,985
I love him!

330
00:34:05,208 --> 00:34:07,726
Drive the devil away, sister. Wake up!

331
00:34:08,429 --> 00:34:10,319
Otherwise God will judge you and him, both.

332
00:34:10,379 --> 00:34:11,949
Get back to your
brothers and sisters!

333
00:34:13,125 --> 00:34:15,750
Ministry of Culture of the UkrSSR
Donetsk Regional Museum

334
00:34:15,792 --> 00:34:19,448
Kids, make a circle! 
Do not touch the exhibits, 
do not ask questions.

335
00:34:20,326 --> 00:34:22,981
Well, this part of the museum 
is dedicated to the Donbas history

336
00:34:24,443 --> 00:34:27,636
Peter the Great issued a decree in 1723.

337
00:34:28,603 --> 00:34:31,923
"To the Dnipro river,
and its tributaries,

338
00:34:32,656 --> 00:34:37,377
to explore and search for black coal
- assign deacon Kapustin".

339
00:34:38,779 --> 00:34:41,089
And now we move to the section
"Takeover in Donbas".

340
00:34:42,042 --> 00:34:43,453
Lenin addressed miners:

341
00:34:44,190 --> 00:34:47,100
"Coal is a true bread for the industry".

342
00:34:48,994 --> 00:34:51,930
Flower... Stiopa, come here!

343
00:34:53,177 --> 00:34:54,802
Flower on a stone.

344
00:35:03,083 --> 00:35:07,122
<i>We are saying goodbye,
getting ready to go,</i>

345
00:35:07,250 --> 00:35:11,109
<i>happier and more beautiful,
the world has ever known.</i>

346
00:35:11,500 --> 00:35:15,351
<i>Friends, we're going,
and promise in our hearts,</i>

347
00:35:15,438 --> 00:35:19,678
<i>that we'll stay
seventeen forever.</i>

348
00:36:06,944 --> 00:36:09,207
- Baraniuk. Come here.
- What?

349
00:36:09,333 --> 00:36:11,492
By the rule
we got to celebrate victory.

350
00:36:12,708 --> 00:36:15,886
It’s an idea! Fellas, come here!

351
00:36:16,584 --> 00:36:19,726
- So, we have to organize.
- Don't worry.

352
00:36:21,449 --> 00:36:23,408
We did it!

353
00:36:24,068 --> 00:36:25,998
- Come on.
- Sure!

354
00:36:42,770 --> 00:36:45,609
- Who made all the guys drunk?
- I’ve treated them.

355
00:36:46,666 --> 00:36:47,697
Me.

356
00:36:48,635 --> 00:36:51,029
Following old miner’s tradition.

357
00:36:51,592 --> 00:36:53,013
Just look.

358
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:56,553
The guys won the banner,
they worked as devils -

359
00:36:57,037 --> 00:36:59,047
and nobody rewarded them
even a drink.

360
00:36:59,183 --> 00:37:01,760
32 workers
didn’t come to work today!

361
00:37:04,109 --> 00:37:07,743
32? Losers!

362
00:37:08,899 --> 00:37:10,922
As you see, we’ve come.

363
00:37:12,008 --> 00:37:16,484
Mademoiselle Komsomol leader
is mourning the authority she's lost.

364
00:37:23,449 --> 00:37:25,801
Where did you come from?

365
00:37:29,945 --> 00:37:31,663
You’re all such a waste and 
belong to the mine dump.

366
00:37:35,208 --> 00:37:36,710
To the mine dump!

367
00:37:45,482 --> 00:37:48,604
Hrysha, come on.
Why are you upset?

368
00:37:50,705 --> 00:37:54,471
It’s... a Komsomol media.

369
00:37:55,121 --> 00:37:57,231
- Get used to self-criticism.
- Shut up!

370
00:38:01,387 --> 00:38:02,768
Hrysha, where are you going?

371
00:38:04,718 --> 00:38:07,137
To the spoil tip
means to the spoil tip!

372
00:38:08,829 --> 00:38:10,548
Hrysha? Where you go?

373
00:38:16,798 --> 00:38:18,260
Hrysha!

374
00:38:20,022 --> 00:38:21,571
Hry...

375
00:39:21,341 --> 00:39:23,158
Guys, over here!

376
00:39:26,796 --> 00:39:29,421
- What’s up?
- Look, it’s Hryva!

377
00:39:30,826 --> 00:39:34,861
- Let's take him to the hostel.
- Go ahead! One, two, heave.

378
00:39:37,092 --> 00:39:38,330
Who’s there?

379
00:39:47,667 --> 00:39:50,740
- Serhii? What’s up?
- Excuse me.

380
00:39:52,306 --> 00:39:54,538
Can you give us a needle and black thread?

381
00:39:55,131 --> 00:39:58,839
- The jacket was torn...
- Let me see.

382
00:40:03,327 --> 00:40:04,524
Come back in an hour.

383
00:40:05,722 --> 00:40:07,579
Maybe, I’ll bring it myself, fine?

384
00:40:08,184 --> 00:40:09,850
Fine, thanks.

385
00:40:13,237 --> 00:40:16,640
- Serhii? Did anybody fight?
- No.

386
00:40:17,618 --> 00:40:19,409
My honest Komsomol word - no!

387
00:40:20,687 --> 00:40:22,800
Well, and I see rock
under the glass.

388
00:40:23,902 --> 00:40:25,700
300.000 years old!

389
00:40:26,647 --> 00:40:29,898
And an imprint on it - the flower.

390
00:40:31,769 --> 00:40:37,240
I’ll find such a rock and send it
to the village. Let them enjoy!

391
00:40:41,305 --> 00:40:45,330
Well, fine, turn off the light.
Let’s sleep.

392
00:40:53,131 --> 00:40:56,360
Year 1723. Kapustin.

393
00:40:57,264 --> 00:41:00,522
Russian. Named Hryshka.

394
00:41:01,043 --> 00:41:04,158
He was the first who discovered
black coal in the Donetsk steppe.

395
00:41:04,495 --> 00:41:07,295
He should have been commemorated 
in the book of miners’ glory!

396
00:41:07,875 --> 00:41:08,991
But they’ve forgotten...

397
00:41:09,692 --> 00:41:11,333
Not fair.

398
00:42:34,232 --> 00:42:37,386
Mit’ka, are you asleep? Hey!

399
00:42:39,542 --> 00:42:41,534
On January 26, this year

400
00:42:41,583 --> 00:42:45,454
in the funeral day of the leader
to USSR Council of people's commissars

401
00:42:46,062 --> 00:42:48,008
Vladimir Lenin...

402
00:42:50,472 --> 00:42:52,265
the mines...

403
00:42:53,616 --> 00:42:55,651
will not work...

404
00:44:06,553 --> 00:44:09,070
- Good morning, aunt Dasha!
- Good morning, Liudochka!

405
00:44:09,442 --> 00:44:10,962
Wipe the feet.

406
00:44:51,553 --> 00:44:53,974
- Greetings, Pavlo Fedorovych.
- Greetings.

407
00:44:54,937 --> 00:44:57,656
- Pouring the flowers.
- They also want to drink.

408
00:45:05,021 --> 00:45:08,072
- Don’t be surprised, Pavlo Fedorovych.
- Nothing to surprise. Everything is clear.

409
00:45:08,516 --> 00:45:10,613
- Really? Do you know, why I'm here?
- Already know.

410
00:45:11,479 --> 00:45:12,908
No, you can’t know this.

411
00:45:13,164 --> 00:45:15,034
Don’t even try to show sagacity.

412
00:45:16,402 --> 00:45:19,730
- Take me to work in the mine.
- What?

413
00:45:20,369 --> 00:45:22,485
You’ve said you know everything!

414
00:45:24,713 --> 00:45:26,468
No, I didn't know this...

415
00:45:27,375 --> 00:45:28,859
Why do you need it?

416
00:45:29,918 --> 00:45:34,537
- Is it easier to make lads drunk?
- I’m going to work here!

417
00:45:38,920 --> 00:45:41,754
Well... I’m not against.

418
00:45:42,781 --> 00:45:47,050
But you know, I’m a chief only.

419
00:45:48,444 --> 00:45:52,322
There are...
Communist Party head, Komsomol...

420
00:45:52,708 --> 00:45:54,394
- Who?
- Komsomol lead, for example.

421
00:45:54,916 --> 00:45:58,171
We build Komsomolska mine here.
She must be asked.

422
00:45:58,445 --> 00:46:01,023
- Pavlo Fedorovych! Don’t!
- Why ‘don’t’?

423
00:46:01,083 --> 00:46:02,771
- Don’t!
- We should.

424
00:46:09,168 --> 00:46:10,884
Look, how signaling works.

425
00:46:11,415 --> 00:46:13,708
Three knocks - Komsomol lead comes.

426
00:46:14,950 --> 00:46:17,472
Four knocks - accountant appears.

427
00:46:26,642 --> 00:46:30,850
- Did you call, Pavlo Fedorovych?
- Called. Need your advise.

428
00:46:38,417 --> 00:46:40,258
Here is Hrysha Hryva...

429
00:46:41,119 --> 00:46:43,064
He‘s hiring to our mine
as a tunneller.

430
00:46:43,205 --> 00:46:45,043
- I do not hire!
- Quiet.

431
00:46:47,832 --> 00:46:49,794
He came to be hired.

432
00:46:54,432 --> 00:46:55,804
What do Komsomol think?

433
00:46:57,593 --> 00:47:00,214
- Let’s hire?
- I think...

434
00:47:02,500 --> 00:47:05,530
Let’s hire. With the only condition.

435
00:47:05,914 --> 00:47:09,413
Interesting! What conditions
can you demand for?

436
00:47:12,233 --> 00:47:15,713
Two times. Chief engineer is calling.

437
00:47:16,406 --> 00:47:18,882
- You talk here...
- Pavlo Fedorovych.

438
00:47:18,958 --> 00:47:21,279
- Just a moment!
- Pavlo Fedorovych!

439
00:47:23,775 --> 00:47:24,892
Pardon.

440
00:47:38,280 --> 00:47:39,425
For good memories.

441
00:47:43,981 --> 00:47:45,113
What's this?

442
00:47:47,691 --> 00:47:49,107
Why are you like this?

443
00:47:50,693 --> 00:47:52,507
Why are you so messed up?

444
00:47:54,186 --> 00:47:56,117
Brilliant work - and drinking!

445
00:47:56,865 --> 00:47:59,952
What’s this? How to understand this?

446
00:48:08,700 --> 00:48:09,877
I love you.

447
00:48:12,975 --> 00:48:14,687
Don’t you dare to speak of love!

448
00:48:15,125 --> 00:48:17,179
Do you hear? Don’t!

449
00:48:21,191 --> 00:48:22,191
So what?

450
00:48:23,145 --> 00:48:26,260
Shell we hire
Hryhorii Hryva to the mine?

451
00:48:28,687 --> 00:48:30,839
Your decision, Pavlo Fedorovych.

452
00:48:31,794 --> 00:48:33,413
Hryva. Hryva!

453
00:48:38,011 --> 00:48:39,312
What's this?

454
00:48:40,661 --> 00:48:42,218
- It’s a keepsake...
- Give it here.

455
00:48:52,951 --> 00:48:54,132
Just look.

456
00:48:58,806 --> 00:48:59,980
A flower.

457
00:49:02,203 --> 00:49:04,296
300.000 years old.

458
00:49:05,747 --> 00:49:06,884
Ah, Liuda...

459
00:49:08,469 --> 00:49:09,960
Hryva is a poet.

460
00:49:11,073 --> 00:49:13,164
But you didn't got it.

461
00:49:20,208 --> 00:49:22,272
<i>Rise up on your toes...</i>

462
00:49:23,183 --> 00:49:26,481
<i>Hands to the side and down.
Stand the full feet.</i>

463
00:49:27,973 --> 00:49:30,158
<i>Stretch.</i>

464
00:49:32,828 --> 00:49:36,173
- Are they sleeping?
- Returned from the nightshift.

465
00:49:39,036 --> 00:49:41,301
Mummy! Do you know these guys?

466
00:49:44,358 --> 00:49:46,265
Sure, each of them.

467
00:49:47,083 --> 00:49:50,732
He’s from Poltava. Serhii Marchenko.

468
00:49:51,227 --> 00:49:53,939
Writer, composes poetry.

469
00:49:54,936 --> 00:49:58,058
And that one - with an accent,
dark-haired...

470
00:49:59,326 --> 00:50:00,863
he is from amateur activity.

471
00:50:03,035 --> 00:50:04,739
Dances on the tiptoes.

472
00:50:06,078 --> 00:50:09,218
And there... chubby guy.

473
00:50:10,092 --> 00:50:13,641
Koval’. Almost a child.

474
00:50:15,579 --> 00:50:18,325
<i>Dispatcher calling the foreman.</i>

475
00:50:18,821 --> 00:50:20,635
- Serhii Marchenko.
- Me.

476
00:50:23,792 --> 00:50:26,000
- Black-haired, dancing
the tiptoes - who's the one?

477
00:50:26,023 --> 00:50:27,056
Dzhaparidze?

478
00:50:27,105 --> 00:50:28,541
- Dzhaparidze.
- Me!

479
00:50:29,813 --> 00:50:31,504
- Baraniuk Hennadii.
- Me!

480
00:50:32,078 --> 00:50:33,438
- Kusenko.
- Me!

481
00:50:33,633 --> 00:50:35,076
- Potapov.
- Me!

482
00:50:35,125 --> 00:50:36,565
- Koval’.
- Me.

483
00:50:40,500 --> 00:50:42,664
What a gang! The hottest!

484
00:50:53,958 --> 00:50:56,458
What a gang! Nothing to say.

485
00:50:58,458 --> 00:51:00,347
Fine, go away!

486
00:51:03,552 --> 00:51:05,008
It’s your foreman.

487
00:51:06,132 --> 00:51:08,735
- Hryhorii Hryva, tunneler.
- Pavlo Fedorovych...

488
00:51:08,784 --> 00:51:10,968
How many of you per pound, guys?

489
00:51:14,292 --> 00:51:16,653
- Thank you, Pavlo Fedorovych...
- Pavlo Fedorovych!

490
00:51:17,125 --> 00:51:19,583
<i>Odesa is calling.</i>

491
00:51:19,661 --> 00:51:21,859
- It’s unfair.
- What’s unfair?

492
00:51:23,376 --> 00:51:25,398
What kind of men did you give him?

493
00:51:27,917 --> 00:51:30,125
Do you hear? All are laughing.

494
00:51:31,309 --> 00:51:32,605
Let’s see.

495
00:51:47,093 --> 00:51:49,535
<i>Hold on, it’s dark in the mine!</i>

496
00:51:50,000 --> 00:51:52,201
<i>Can you differ coal and rock?</i>

497
00:51:52,958 --> 00:51:55,286
Laughing? Well-well...

498
00:51:56,367 --> 00:51:57,679
Come on, guys.

499
00:51:57,728 --> 00:51:59,700
<i>Bring you some mush, eh?</i>

500
00:52:15,200 --> 00:52:17,928
Guys, I will tell... the thing.

501
00:52:19,687 --> 00:52:23,007
All the world’s beauty
comes from human.

502
00:52:25,016 --> 00:52:27,632
Gagarin raised to cosmos.

503
00:52:28,521 --> 00:52:30,062
And us - under the ground.

504
00:52:31,591 --> 00:52:32,842
So it means...

505
00:52:34,010 --> 00:52:35,632
that all the world’s beauty...

506
00:52:36,833 --> 00:52:38,917
comes from us, bros.

507
00:52:40,034 --> 00:52:43,645
The thing is to believe
in your own force.

508
00:52:45,286 --> 00:52:48,748
An then... Everything will be fine then.

509
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:55,531
Hryva will be pushed around!

510
00:52:55,582 --> 00:52:58,116
Stop talking! Better help Arsen!

511
00:52:58,417 --> 00:52:59,725
Why me?

512
00:53:01,276 --> 00:53:02,629
It’s again from Hryva!

513
00:53:03,175 --> 00:53:06,539
- Is it again by accident?
- They are shooting the rats!

514
00:53:08,208 --> 00:53:11,117
Stop chattering! Back to work!

515
00:53:12,914 --> 00:53:14,669
- Turn on!
- Aye!

516
00:53:21,221 --> 00:53:24,000
Hrysha, how did you
overrun us in a whole cycle?

517
00:53:24,388 --> 00:53:26,384
Hear badly, say louder!

518
00:53:28,011 --> 00:53:31,293
How did you manage
to overrun us in a whole cycle?

519
00:53:31,722 --> 00:53:33,316
- How do you know?

520
00:53:33,656 --> 00:53:35,882
- We’ve heard, when you undermined.

521
00:53:38,556 --> 00:53:39,761
Guys!

522
00:53:40,917 --> 00:53:43,878
Hear? They want our secrets.

523
00:53:45,208 --> 00:53:48,132
Dude, perhaps you
want your back washed?

524
00:53:48,750 --> 00:53:52,561
- Did you forget to laugh?
- Forgot!

525
00:54:12,624 --> 00:54:15,785
Hrysha! Hrysha...

526
00:54:22,859 --> 00:54:26,734
Where have you been lost?

527
00:54:28,205 --> 00:54:31,346
Hrysha, let’s go?

528
00:54:33,313 --> 00:54:35,962
- For clearness.
- Piss off...

529
00:54:37,029 --> 00:54:38,196
- Guardian angel...

530
00:54:38,872 --> 00:54:40,613
- What’s wrong?
- Just go your way!

531
00:54:41,505 --> 00:54:45,506
What’s up? Hrysha? Wait!

532
00:54:48,493 --> 00:54:50,058
Why are you cocky?

533
00:54:53,670 --> 00:54:56,265
You’ve got fellas!

534
00:54:59,783 --> 00:55:02,694
Just wait! We’ll meet again!

535
00:55:43,877 --> 00:55:45,117
Come in.

536
00:55:47,017 --> 00:55:48,190
Come in.

537
00:55:51,817 --> 00:55:54,049
Hryva? Come in.

538
00:56:01,543 --> 00:56:04,754
- How are you?
- Fine, I’ve just dropped in...

539
00:56:05,585 --> 00:56:09,913
- Sorry, am I bothering?
- No-no, sit.

540
00:56:23,451 --> 00:56:26,649
Stendhal. "Red and Black".

541
00:56:27,869 --> 00:56:29,627
You have to read it.

542
00:56:30,889 --> 00:56:32,345
I watched the film.

543
00:56:34,147 --> 00:56:35,519
Good fellow.

544
00:56:38,808 --> 00:56:41,326
Can’t catch the second series.

545
00:56:44,090 --> 00:56:45,350
Listen, Hryva.

546
00:56:51,143 --> 00:56:55,225
- Why don’t you apply for the apartment?
- Why do I need it?

547
00:56:56,913 --> 00:56:58,181
Mother is in the village.

548
00:57:00,623 --> 00:57:01,623
Father...

549
00:57:03,104 --> 00:57:04,104
died...

550
00:57:11,238 --> 00:57:12,238
Write.

551
00:57:14,146 --> 00:57:17,216
I apply to provide me
with living space...

552
00:57:19,287 --> 00:57:22,853
...on the territory
of Dobryi Shliakh village.

553
00:57:28,885 --> 00:57:30,139
Family members:

554
00:57:32,730 --> 00:57:35,745
Mother... dependent...

555
00:57:38,939 --> 00:57:42,370
- What’s her name?
- Mariia Mykolaivna.

556
00:57:46,331 --> 00:57:47,331
Sign.

557
00:57:52,943 --> 00:57:57,484
Here we are. Now I’ll walk through
the village with a pink lamp-shade.

558
00:57:58,178 --> 00:58:02,691
- Why the pink one?
- I didn’t see another.

559
00:58:06,613 --> 00:58:08,423
Mark 2 for the audition.

560
00:58:11,449 --> 00:58:12,776
Re-write.

561
00:58:13,958 --> 00:58:17,157
- "You" in capital letter.
- Come on.

562
00:59:55,375 --> 00:59:57,495
Hey, come on!

563
00:59:58,833 --> 01:00:01,559
Guest in the house,
a host out of house.

564
01:00:02,785 --> 01:00:03,981
Turn on!

565
01:00:11,479 --> 01:00:13,506
Happy housewarming!

566
01:00:14,173 --> 01:00:15,743
Daddy!

567
01:00:18,500 --> 01:00:20,727
Oh my God!

568
01:00:21,269 --> 01:00:24,378
- Are you my daughter?!
- Don’t worry, I’ll wash.

569
01:00:25,648 --> 01:00:28,741
Foreman, don’t worry!
He’s her father!

570
01:00:30,035 --> 01:00:32,714
I’m not worrying.
No reason to worry.

571
01:00:34,809 --> 01:00:37,086
Let’s have lunch now.
And the concert in the evening.

572
01:00:37,399 --> 01:00:40,589
Listen, Liudochka.
I’ve come not for long.

573
01:00:41,748 --> 01:00:44,232
I leave today. We need to talk.

574
01:00:44,917 --> 01:00:46,267
- Liuda?
- What do you want?

575
01:00:46,375 --> 01:00:47,777
- Hello.
- Hello.

576
01:00:48,000 --> 01:00:51,725
- We go to bosses and need a car.
- Go to the dispatcher, I agreed yet.

577
01:00:52,041 --> 01:00:56,781
Go ahead! Daddy, go to that house,
I will come up, ok?

578
01:01:04,922 --> 01:01:06,195
Hey, look…

579
01:01:21,052 --> 01:01:22,762
When are you going home?

580
01:01:24,449 --> 01:01:27,746
Daddy, do you think it’s possible?

581
01:01:29,689 --> 01:01:31,344
Kiss mom,
I'll come on vacations soon.

582
01:01:31,478 --> 01:01:33,237
- Alone?
- Don’t worry, alone!

583
01:01:35,153 --> 01:01:37,207
You better be, don’t linger.

584
01:01:37,680 --> 01:01:40,022
- Hold the milk, please!
- Sure. Bye.

585
01:01:43,300 --> 01:01:44,934
Come, we’re waiting.

586
01:02:43,357 --> 01:02:45,939
Lets start
the "Holy Gifts" concert!

587
01:02:45,988 --> 01:02:49,063
Dear, where are you pulling me?
Where are you pulling me?

588
01:02:59,779 --> 01:03:01,282
God, accept our offerings!

589
01:03:06,255 --> 01:03:09,711
- Offer!
- Offer!

590
01:03:13,167 --> 01:03:16,780
Why did you do all this stuff?
Why?! It’s not true!

591
01:03:17,292 --> 01:03:19,809
Stop! It’s not true!

592
01:03:22,679 --> 01:03:24,362
- Chmykh!
- What?

593
01:03:35,290 --> 01:03:38,866
- Well, what’s going on there?
- Satire.

594
01:03:40,473 --> 01:03:43,152
- You look very alike.
- Hey-hey!

595
01:03:44,596 --> 01:03:47,821
It’s Arsen’s pranks...
How is Khrystyna?

596
01:03:49,387 --> 01:03:50,703
Differently.

597
01:03:52,481 --> 01:03:55,325
- Well, act. Understand?
- Understand!

598
01:03:55,825 --> 01:03:57,329
Just carefully.

599
01:04:04,704 --> 01:04:07,225
Khrystyna!
Khrystyna, where do you go?

600
01:04:08,495 --> 01:04:10,262
- Where?
- Don’t you follow me...

601
01:04:10,311 --> 01:04:12,500
You do not know,
how things can end up.

602
01:04:18,750 --> 01:04:20,801
Brother! Save me, my brother!

603
01:04:20,926 --> 01:04:23,716
I’ve trusted them, but they deride us.
They do not understand us.

604
01:04:25,167 --> 01:04:26,288
My sister...

605
01:04:26,958 --> 01:04:29,150
I haven’t seen you
for so long, my dear.

606
01:04:29,456 --> 01:04:32,876
- Forgive me! Forgive!
- God forgives you.

607
01:04:36,042 --> 01:04:40,537
If only you’ve returned
truly and forever in your heart...

608
01:04:41,097 --> 01:04:43,497
- ...to God.
- I’ve returned.

609
01:04:43,806 --> 01:04:48,192
- I’ve returned for all my life.
- Thank you, thank you, sister.

610
01:04:49,390 --> 01:04:52,369
- You’ll be my wife...
- Wife?!

611
01:04:53,691 --> 01:04:56,865
- You’ll be!
- Give your sacred blessing, father.

612
01:04:57,269 --> 01:04:59,396
- Daddy...
- Bless you.

613
01:04:59,792 --> 01:05:03,862
- Daddy, are you here?
- Bless you forever.

614
01:05:05,792 --> 01:05:08,011
- Wife...
- Wife.

615
01:05:08,557 --> 01:05:12,062
You are my wife now.
Father’s blessing is sacral.

616
01:05:12,377 --> 01:05:15,038
- How can it be?
- Sacral and inviolable.

617
01:05:15,746 --> 01:05:19,560
Daddy! What happiness
are you talking about?

618
01:05:20,456 --> 01:05:21,579
Daddy...

619
01:05:23,409 --> 01:05:25,062
What happiness?

620
01:05:27,666 --> 01:05:29,015
Come with me.

621
01:05:46,042 --> 01:05:47,042
Oh Dear!

622
01:05:49,077 --> 01:05:52,203
- And You see all these!
- Khrystyna!

623
01:05:55,584 --> 01:05:58,817
- Come to yourself, sister!
- Shut up!

624
01:06:30,667 --> 01:06:32,275
Arsen Zahornyi?

625
01:06:36,750 --> 01:06:38,356
- Let’s go.
- Where?

626
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:40,593
We have to talk.

627
01:06:41,917 --> 01:06:43,140
Let’s go.

628
01:07:19,007 --> 01:07:21,078
Stop, stop! Stop, Hrysha, hurry up!

629
01:07:21,125 --> 01:07:24,222
They are hitting Arsen now, come on!

630
01:07:31,292 --> 01:07:35,898
<i>In Ural, autonomous republics
of the middle and bottom Volga regions</i>

631
01:07:36,214 --> 01:07:38,871
<i>there is low cloud and warm weather.</i>

632
01:07:39,066 --> 01:07:41,843
<i>In the north-west region
of the USSR European territory...</i>

633
01:07:46,560 --> 01:07:50,866
<i>...in Belarus and bigger part of Ukraine
it is warm without fallouts.</i>

634
01:07:59,917 --> 01:08:03,095
<i>...in the east of the central part
of European territory of the Union...</i>

635
01:08:07,583 --> 01:08:10,538
<i>...termination of the fallouts
is expected,..</i>

636
01:08:14,542 --> 01:08:18,509
<i>...but rains are expected
in the east of central part</i>

637
01:08:18,847 --> 01:08:20,831
<i>and northern regions of Ukraine.</i>

638
01:08:21,519 --> 01:08:26,580
<i>Rest of the terrain in Ukraine,
Moldova, Crimean sea coast...</i>

639
01:08:28,167 --> 01:08:29,411
Hrysha!

640
01:08:37,208 --> 01:08:41,059
Comrade Varchenko, good afternoon!
You’ve predicted it.

641
01:08:41,414 --> 01:08:43,429
You see? They are breaking.

642
01:08:46,601 --> 01:08:51,774
Pavlo Fedorovych, did you hear, what
happened in the eve, some confusion?

643
01:08:56,069 --> 01:08:59,696
- Stop fooling, Zabroda.
- What do you mean?

644
01:09:04,375 --> 01:09:06,663
Your beliefs - it's your business.

645
01:09:07,959 --> 01:09:13,067
But when you destroy human souls -
our business begins! Go!

646
01:09:14,125 --> 01:09:15,781
What do you mean?

647
01:09:18,182 --> 01:09:21,587
- Well...
- Wow! What’s this?

648
01:09:22,873 --> 01:09:24,023
This?

649
01:09:25,250 --> 01:09:27,140
At night in the vault!

650
01:09:28,769 --> 01:09:31,116
- Uncle Pasha?
- What?

651
01:09:31,542 --> 01:09:34,196
I can't get a note here.
Please show me.

652
01:09:36,193 --> 01:09:38,221
Ugh you, dudes.

653
01:09:40,896 --> 01:09:43,526
Pasha Chmykh... does the best.

654
01:09:45,146 --> 01:09:46,146
Listen.

655
01:09:52,292 --> 01:09:55,882
And now... continue playing with joy...

656
01:09:56,539 --> 01:09:58,715
and come with us to the police!

657
01:10:00,413 --> 01:10:01,656
Wha-a-at?

658
01:10:06,284 --> 01:10:08,407
- Come on, guys!
- Play!

659
01:10:11,167 --> 01:10:12,851
Play with joy.

660
01:10:17,083 --> 01:10:20,210
- More joy, more!
- Go ahead.

661
01:10:24,250 --> 01:10:25,757
Go-go!

662
01:10:41,432 --> 01:10:44,470
It seems... everything happened
just tomorrow.

663
01:10:47,250 --> 01:10:49,357
- What were you afraid of?
- Presbyter.

664
01:10:51,223 --> 01:10:53,481
But we are stronger
than him, Khrystyna.

665
01:10:53,757 --> 01:10:55,665
- What are you saying?
- Stronger.

666
01:10:56,831 --> 01:10:59,202
There is no God in the sky,
believe me.

667
01:11:09,665 --> 01:11:11,938
- Why are you here?
- To see him?

668
01:11:14,438 --> 01:11:18,682
- Yes, him.
- Pass, please. Milk.

669
01:11:20,653 --> 01:11:22,140
Milk?

670
01:11:23,083 --> 01:11:24,519
Where you’ve gone?

671
01:11:25,208 --> 01:11:28,343
Doctor! Welcome to my housewarming!

672
01:11:28,606 --> 01:11:30,114
Thanks. I’ll come.

673
01:11:40,033 --> 01:11:41,972
I was asked to pass you milk.

674
01:11:45,558 --> 01:11:47,937
- Go...
- Fresh.

675
01:11:55,792 --> 01:11:57,843
Drink immediately, until it is warm.

676
01:12:01,666 --> 01:12:05,309
I thought you're inviting doctor...
to the wedding.

677
01:12:12,492 --> 01:12:17,039
You just drink, in small drinks,
don’t hurry, don’t gulp...

678
01:12:20,625 --> 01:12:23,117
Nurse, we’re just for a minute,
please, please!

679
01:12:24,625 --> 01:12:26,167
- Hi!
- Hi!

680
01:12:29,955 --> 01:12:33,598
Here. M-i-l-k.

681
01:12:50,340 --> 01:12:53,020
